        /* 
        
        B. Write a JavaScript function to get the first 'n' elements of an array. Make it arrow.
        
        C. Write a JavaScript program to compute the average marks of the students in a class.
         Then, the average will be used to determine the corresponding grade:
        
            Muy deficiente: <2
            Insuficiente: <5
            Suficiente: <6
            Bien: <7
            Notable: <9
            Sobresaliente: from 9 on.
        
        D. Write a JavaScript program to sum the common multiples of 3 and 5 under 1000. 
        
        E. Write a JavaScript program which accept a number as input and insert dashes (-) between each two even numbers. 
        For example, if you accept 025468 the output should be 0-254-6-8.
        
